WEBVTT

00:01.101 --> 00:02.796
Myname is Michael Westen.

00:02.869 --> 00:05.531
I used to be a spy until--

00:05.605 --> 00:08.096
- [ Man ] We got a burn notice on you.
You're blacklisted.
- [ Whistles ]

00:08.173 --> 00:10.574
[Michael Narrating]
Whenyou're burned,you've got nothing--

00:10.643 --> 00:13.203
no cash, no credit, nojob history..

00:13.279 --> 00:16.407
- You're stuck in whatever city
they decide to dump you in.
- Where am I?

00:16.483 --> 00:18.110
Miam i.

00:18.184 --> 00:20.812
You do whatever work comes your way.

00:20.887 --> 00:23.549
- You rely on anyone who's still talking to you--
- [ Laughs ]

00:23.623 --> 00:26.490
- a trigger-happy ex-girlfriend--
- Should we shoot them?

00:26.559 --> 00:29.392
an old friend who used to
inform on you to the F.B.I.--

00:29.462 --> 00:31.760
You know spies.
Bunch of bitchy little girls.

00:31.831 --> 00:34.163
- Family too--
- Hey, is that your mom again?

00:34.234 --> 00:36.395
- ifyou're desperate.
- Someone needs your help, Michael.

00:36.469 --> 00:38.937
Bottom line:
Untilyou figure out who burnedyou...

00:40.974 --> 00:43.272
you're not going anywhere.

00:43.343 --> 00:46.801
?? [ Man Singing In Spanish ]

00:46.880 --> 00:49.246
[ Michael Narrating]
Getting information is all about fitting in.

00:49.315 --> 00:53.081
Ifyou're hunting for intel in the Middle East,
that means a beard and a djel laba.

00:53.153 --> 00:55.178
Ifyou're doing it on South Beach,
you're probably wearing...

00:55.255 --> 00:57.189
a swimsuit and flip-flops.

00:57.257 --> 01:00.784
You thi nk the sarong is too m uch?
Suddenly, I 'm feeling overdressed.

01:00.860 --> 01:03.454
You look fine, Fi.
Besides, we're here on business.

01:03.530 --> 01:05.521
What is the big deal with this bomber?

01:05.598 --> 01:08.192
Ifwe looked for everyone who tried
to kill you, we'd do nothing else.

01:08.268 --> 01:10.463
I need to find out what this guy knows.

01:10.537 --> 01:13.131
[ Fiona ] Well, ifthere's anyone in Miami
who can track down a bomber...

01:13.206 --> 01:15.197
it's our old friend Seymour here.

01:15.275 --> 01:18.870
Hope he's still not mad about the face
full of gunpowder last time we dropped by.

01:18.945 --> 01:22.108
Well, he was pretty enchanted with you
once upon a time.

01:22.182 --> 01:24.673
Pretty enchanted with me? Yeah.

01:24.751 --> 01:27.777
He showed it when he attacked me
with a baseball bat.

01:27.854 --> 01:29.788
Will you do my shoulders?

01:34.828 --> 01:37.092
You know, Fi, if, uh--

01:37.163 --> 01:39.961
ifyou wanna talk
about what happened the other night--

01:40.033 --> 01:44.333
There's nothing to talk about.
We were just blowing offsome steam, right?

01:46.005 --> 01:47.996
We should go in.

01:51.211 --> 01:53.839
??[Hip-hop On Stereo ]

01:58.685 --> 02:01.586
[Michael Narrating]
When it comes to intelligence gathering...

02:01.654 --> 02:03.588
you can't hold grudges.

02:03.656 --> 02:06.056
The guy who hityou with
a baseball batyesterday...

02:06.126 --> 02:10.027
could be an information source today.

02:10.096 --> 02:13.259
- Fi, you wanna take care of--
- Yeah, I 'll take care of Mr. Security over there...

02:13.333 --> 02:15.426
while you say hello to Seymour.

02:20.640 --> 02:24.269
- Hello, Seymour.
- Security!

02:24.344 --> 02:27.040
[ Guests Gasping ]

02:33.286 --> 02:36.346
Nice goin',Jackass!
You know, I learned a thing or two...

02:36.422 --> 02:38.686
- after the last timeyou kicked his ass.
- What's that?

02:38.758 --> 02:42.353
When it comes to mypersonalsecurity,
I gotta take care ofthings myself.

02:42.428 --> 02:44.055
[ Hammer Cocks ]

02:44.130 --> 02:47.190
- You got hollow points in there.
- Oh, you can tell just by looking--

02:47.267 --> 02:49.758
No, I can't. But I can distract you
long enough to take it.

02:49.836 --> 02:52.930
Now, I just need help tracking
someone down, Seymour. That's it.

02:53.006 --> 02:56.134
You are such a badass.
It's kind of awesome.

02:56.209 --> 02:58.905
You need my help? Okay.

02:58.978 --> 03:03.938
- One condition.
You gotta teach me some ofthese moves.
- Sure.

03:04.017 --> 03:07.043
All right. What's everybody starin' at?
This is a party.

03:07.120 --> 03:10.783
I'm sorry, Mike. What are we doing again?

03:10.857 --> 03:14.554
I need help tracking someone--
an explosives expert, Derek Poole.

03:14.627 --> 03:16.891
Oh, right. A manhunt. I love it.

03:16.963 --> 03:19.625
Okay, first, you're gonna have to
front me some cash to spread around.

03:19.699 --> 03:23.191
It opens doors. No? Okay.

03:23.269 --> 03:26.136
I'll frontyou,
because I knowyou're good for it.

03:26.206 --> 03:28.936
But we are gonna have
to be in constant dialogue, Mike, okay?

03:29.008 --> 03:32.774
You and me, badasses in this together.

03:32.845 --> 03:38.147
All right,Jackass,
you see how theyjust laid you out again?

03:38.218 --> 03:41.244
That is called teamwork, people.

03:41.321 --> 03:44.620
And it is a beautiful thing.
So, up and at 'em.

03:44.691 --> 03:47.319
Hit the blender, make some smoothies.

03:47.393 --> 03:50.328
You like mango? Mango.

03:56.135 --> 03:58.399
Fi. Fi, I need a favor.

03:58.471 --> 04:00.405
Uh, I need to put some money together.

04:00.473 --> 04:02.134
- Seymour said he'd front you.
- Yeah.

04:02.208 --> 04:05.200
Seymour's not the type
of guy I wanna owe money to long-term.

04:05.278 --> 04:07.746
You wanna borrow money?

04:07.814 --> 04:10.442
Ifyou need cash,
you can get a job like the rest of us.

04:10.516 --> 04:13.076
I can't fill out a W-2.
Ifthe people who burned me...

04:13.152 --> 04:16.212
find out I'm looking for
a job, they'll wonderwhy I need money.

04:16.289 --> 04:18.951
I just passed on a gig for some art dealer.

04:19.024 --> 04:22.290
Someone's stealing paper clips
or something dull. Pay's good.

04:22.362 --> 04:25.160
You take a job under a cover I.D.,
no one needs to know.

04:25.231 --> 04:27.165
- You're the best.
- Mm-hmm.

04:27.233 --> 04:29.929
I expect a commission, Michael.

04:35.441 --> 04:38.808
Mike, doyou have to workwith Seymour?
I mean, the guy's unstable.

04:38.878 --> 04:41.176
He's connected, and he doesn't
mix well with government types.

04:41.247 --> 04:44.148
- Doyou have my new cover I.D.?
- Yes. You're Miles Parker.

04:44.217 --> 04:46.913
Background in corporate espionage.
You're a deskjockey.

04:46.986 --> 04:48.920
Perfect for a cushy office gig.

04:48.988 --> 04:50.717
- Looks good, Sam.
- [ Cell Phone Rings ]

04:52.659 --> 04:55.856
Yeah, Fi, looks like I'm good to go
for that art dealerjob.

04:58.197 --> 05:00.597
Thanks. I'll call you later.
Maybe we can grab dinner.

05:00.667 --> 05:03.602
- [Beeps ]
- So you two are just grabbing dinner?

05:03.670 --> 05:07.902
-Just to debrief.
- Right. Debrief.

05:11.244 --> 05:13.178
[Michael Narrating]
There are a lot ofadvantages...

05:13.246 --> 05:15.840
to taking on a new identity
whenyou take a newjob.

05:15.915 --> 05:17.974
You can tailoryou résumé to the position...

05:18.051 --> 05:19.712
and it gives you a lot offlexibility.

05:19.786 --> 05:24.189
Youjust have to get used
to the idea oflying to every.one you meet.

05:24.257 --> 05:26.919
- I 'm Mi les Parker.
- H i, Mi les Parker.

05:26.993 --> 05:30.622
- I 'm here to see Scott Chandler.
- Mr. Parker.

05:30.697 --> 05:33.063
You came highly recommended.
Scott Chandler.

05:33.132 --> 05:35.930
- Welcome to the gallery.
- Thankyou. Thankyou very much.

05:36.002 --> 05:38.061
Can I getyousomething to drink?

05:38.137 --> 05:42.073
- Coffee? Water? Scotch and soda?
- I'm fine.

05:42.141 --> 05:43.870
[ Beeping ]

05:43.943 --> 05:46.878
Right this way.

05:46.946 --> 05:50.746
Quite the résumé.
Wall Street, Silicon Valley, D.C.

05:50.817 --> 05:54.150
Anyplace where a little information goes
a long way, I've been there to protect it.

05:54.220 --> 05:59.419
- Any P.I. experience?
- A P.I. Iicense comes with
a lot of privacy concerns.

05:59.492 --> 06:02.655
There's a chance anything a private
investigator finds could wind up in court.

06:02.729 --> 06:06.324
Yeah, well, I prefer to resolve this
quickly and quietly as possible.

06:06.399 --> 06:09.493
Quick and quiet--That's what I do.
Tell me aboutyour problem.

06:09.569 --> 06:12.163
A fewweeks ago, I noticed unusual
activity on the computers.

06:12.238 --> 06:14.502
Files moved, log-ins at odd times.

06:14.574 --> 06:17.634
And then, I started hearing
a buzzing sound in my office phone.

06:17.710 --> 06:20.804
- I checked it out.
- Infinity transmitter in its base.

06:20.880 --> 06:22.780
Saw a lot ofthat in the dot-coms.

06:22.849 --> 06:26.307
Whoever installed it didn't isolate the circuit.
You're hearing a little feedback.

06:26.386 --> 06:30.288
I wanna know who planted this.

06:30.356 --> 06:32.620
Any idea what they're looking for?

06:32.692 --> 06:34.785
I sell about $30 million worth ofart a year.

06:34.861 --> 06:38.820
It could be thieves, buyers looking
to lowball a bid, other art dealers.

06:38.898 --> 06:42.129
Too many possibilities.
My business, my reputation...

06:42.201 --> 06:45.932
- depends on information remaining private.
- Let's take a look around.

06:46.005 --> 06:48.838
Now, the gallery's under
24-hourvideo surveillance.

06:48.908 --> 06:50.773
Can't get through here
without someone seeing it.

06:50.843 --> 06:53.277
What about the executive offices?

06:53.346 --> 06:56.907
There's no cameras,
but all the offices are keypad access only.

06:56.983 --> 06:59.577
No one gets in here without me knowing.

06:59.652 --> 07:03.782
Well, somebody has.
Does anybody have a habit ofworking late?

07:03.856 --> 07:06.654
No later than I do.
I'm the first one in, last one out.

07:09.395 --> 07:12.489
So what doyou think, Mr. Parker?
Thinkyou can find whoever's doing this?

07:15.034 --> 07:18.526
- I'll see what I can do. I need
a floor plan ofthe office.
- [Cell Phone Ringing]

07:18.604 --> 07:20.868
I'll have something
by the end oftoday. Excuse me.

07:22.575 --> 07:25.339
- [ Seymour] Alpha, it's Bravo. Over.
- Hello, Seymour.

07:25.411 --> 07:28.244
Chalk one up forthe brotherhood ofbadass,
buddy. I got good news.

07:28.314 --> 07:30.248
You gotta get over here.

07:31.551 --> 07:33.644
?? [ Woman Vocalizing]

07:34.921 --> 07:37.219
So I asked around about that
explosives guy you were looking for.

07:37.290 --> 07:41.317
He does demo for the city,
but he moonlights for the Russian mob.

07:41.394 --> 07:45.888
This is their hangout. He's their go-to guy
when something's gotta go boom.

07:45.965 --> 07:48.024
- Any idea where he's hiding?
- No.

07:48.100 --> 07:51.934
- Seymour, you said you had good news.
- No, I do. He's got a girlfriend.

07:52.004 --> 07:55.064
And they're hot and heavy. They can't
be apart for more than a couple of days...

07:55.141 --> 07:57.075
without some together time,
you know what I'm saying?

07:57.143 --> 07:58.838
- I know what you're saying.
- I bet you do.

07:58.911 --> 08:03.371
You and Fi-- My God.
A molten hot action couple.

08:03.449 --> 08:06.316
I can't even imagine what
it must be like in the bedroom.Just--

08:06.385 --> 08:08.182
- [ Imitates Explosion ]
- Don't do that.

08:08.254 --> 08:10.245
- Right? Am I right?
- We're not together.

08:10.323 --> 08:13.520
Areyou serious?
Oh, my God. You guys are like the-the--

08:13.593 --> 08:16.528
- Bomber's girlfriend. Stay focused.
- There she is.

08:18.297 --> 08:20.094
- Don't point.
- Um--

08:22.468 --> 08:26.097
Bianca. She works here.
Hershift starts in, like, 10 minutes.

08:26.172 --> 08:29.141
Nice work, Seymour.

08:33.946 --> 08:36.744
[Seymour]
Oh, the best part is, myjackass bodyguard...

08:36.816 --> 08:40.876
he's gonna put a tracker under her car
so you can follow her right to him.

08:40.953 --> 08:43.945
He's gonna put a tracking device
under her car in front of the Russian mob?

08:44.023 --> 08:47.322
Oh, he-- But it's cool. I told him,
just pretend like he's tying his shoe.

08:47.393 --> 08:49.327
He's gonna tip her off
that someone's watching.

08:49.395 --> 08:51.727
Keepyour eyes on Bianca,
and no more moves on your own.

08:54.333 --> 08:57.029
[Michael Narrating]
To protectsomeone without blowingyour cover...

08:57.103 --> 09:01.164
you have to come up with a story.--
one that explains what they're doing...

09:01.240 --> 09:04.732
explains whatyou're doing
and gets every.one out in one piece.

09:04.810 --> 09:07.335
- Hey, you forgotyour keys.
- Wait.

09:07.413 --> 09:10.644
- My keys? No, I--
- You forgot your keys on my wife's dresser.

09:10.716 --> 09:13.583
Yeah. Yeah, that remind you?

09:13.653 --> 09:16.178
Ofcourse, not every.one is a born storyteller.

09:16.255 --> 09:18.951
- Go with it. Run.
- But Seymour said to plant a tracker.

09:21.360 --> 09:23.294
[ Laughs ]

09:26.198 --> 09:29.258
And don't let me catch you
near mywife again!

09:32.271 --> 09:35.001
I gotta tell you, this corporate
espionage stuffis kind offun.

09:35.074 --> 09:37.008
You know, there's no guns, no explosions.

09:37.076 --> 09:39.010
It's like going on the kiddy rides
at the carnival.

09:39.078 --> 09:41.876
[ Chuckling ]
So, uh...

09:41.948 --> 09:44.382
any idea how our spy got his way into
the art dealer's office?

09:44.450 --> 09:46.384
I know how I'd do it.

09:46.452 --> 09:48.443
Cleaning crew comes around midnight...

09:48.521 --> 09:51.649
from the service entrance here,
away from the gallery cameras.

09:51.724 --> 09:54.192
Well, that's good, because
then there's no door codes either...

09:54.260 --> 09:56.194
'cause the cleaning crew opens them foryou.

09:56.262 --> 09:58.958
Get in, find a hiding place,
let everyone clear out.

09:59.031 --> 10:01.556
And you got the place to yourself.

10:01.634 --> 10:03.898
[Fiona Sighs ]

10:07.273 --> 10:11.209
As stimulating as all this is, I still don't see
whyyou called me over here, Michael.

10:11.277 --> 10:13.541
It always helps to bounce ideas, Fi.

10:18.684 --> 10:24.088
Uh, I'm gonna grab another beer and, uh,
drink it on the balcony.

10:30.363 --> 10:32.763
Is this about the other night?

10:32.832 --> 10:34.823
Is this about me not staying for breakfast?

10:34.900 --> 10:38.859
Is it so strange that
I would wantyour opinion on a job?

10:40.139 --> 10:43.768
Look me in the eye
and tell me that's all this is.

10:47.079 --> 10:48.910
I have to go see Chandler.

