10:57.356 --> 10:59.916
You think he came in with the cleaning crew.

10:59.992 --> 11:03.689
- Can't believe I was so stupid.
- Whoever did this didn't
come through the gallery.

11:03.763 --> 11:07.096
There's a chance the parking lot cameras
got him at the service entrance.

11:07.166 --> 11:10.829
I'll call the property manager,
set up a time foryou to stop by their office.

11:10.903 --> 11:13.064
You really think
sweeping my office is necessary?

11:13.139 --> 11:16.074
I don't think a phone bug
was the only thing your spy leftyou.

11:16.142 --> 11:18.076
- [ Beeping ]
- I've got dinnerwith a client.

11:18.144 --> 11:20.738
You let me know ifyou find something.

11:22.448 --> 11:24.382
[Michael Narrating]
A bug, in its simplest form...

11:24.450 --> 11:27.385
isjust a microphone attached to a radio.

11:27.453 --> 11:30.786
Effective, but easy to detect
with a frequency scanner.

11:32.858 --> 11:34.416
[ Whi rri ng ]

11:36.696 --> 11:40.427
A more subtle device is
the wireless key logger circuit.

11:40.499 --> 11:42.831
Nearly undetectable and easy to install...

11:42.902 --> 11:45.598
it transmits every. passwordyou type
into the keyboard.

11:47.540 --> 11:51.442
All surveillance devices, though,
share a weakness-- they're machines.

11:51.510 --> 11:54.240
When machines break,
somebody has to fix them.

11:54.313 --> 11:59.012
More spies get caught changing batteries
and fixing wires than any other single activity.

11:59.085 --> 12:01.485
- [ Beeps ]
- Mr. Chandler.

12:01.554 --> 12:05.684
Yeah. I 'm gonna need to work late tonight.

12:30.549 --> 12:32.540
Mr. Parker.

12:32.618 --> 12:34.609
You're the receptionist here, right?
What is it?

12:34.687 --> 12:36.621
Uh, Melanie.

12:36.689 --> 12:39.180
Melanie. Right.
We need to have a conversation.

12:39.258 --> 12:41.726
Okay. I-I-I know this looks crazy...

12:41.794 --> 12:45.321
but, um, I can explain.

12:48.200 --> 12:50.395
Melanie!

12:54.006 --> 12:56.201
Melanie.

12:56.275 --> 12:59.039
Melanie, stop. Stop.
Whateveryou're up to...

12:59.111 --> 13:01.477
it's not worth stabbing me with a letter opener.

13:01.547 --> 13:04.414
Don't tell Chandler! He'll kill me.

13:04.483 --> 13:07.884
Chandler? Yeah, that sounds
a little hard-core for an art dealer.

13:07.953 --> 13:10.012
You don't understand.

13:10.089 --> 13:11.681
He killed my father.

13:20.499 --> 13:22.592
MyfatherwasJ.D. Blake.

13:23.836 --> 13:25.997
The painter? Wow.

13:26.071 --> 13:28.733
How about that?
[ Chuckles ]

13:28.808 --> 13:30.935
Well, Veronica's really into pop art.

13:31.010 --> 13:33.911
You know, you could stand getting out
to a few museums every so often, Mike.

13:33.979 --> 13:36.004
Chandlerwas his art dealer.

13:36.081 --> 13:39.847
Trouble started over a painting
called Ladyin White.

13:39.919 --> 13:43.855
Bids of, like, five, seven million
were coming in before he even finished it.

13:43.923 --> 13:46.289
My dad's health was failing.

13:46.358 --> 13:48.883
But Chandlerjust kept
pressuring him to finish it.

13:48.961 --> 13:51.452
Dad got sick ofit,
said that hewas gonna get a new dealer.

13:51.530 --> 13:53.464
Ooh, that probably
stung Chandler pretty good.

13:53.532 --> 13:56.558
The commission on seven million,
that's a lot of money.

13:56.635 --> 14:01.868
One month later, someone broke into
my dad's loft, beat him to death...

14:01.941 --> 14:04.876
andburneddown his studio.

14:04.944 --> 14:07.242
Ladyin White was reported destroyed.

14:07.313 --> 14:09.474
Cops called it a burglary gone bad.

14:09.548 --> 14:11.277
You think Chandlerwas behind it?

14:11.350 --> 14:15.286
Andhe neverput it togetherthatyou're
J.D. Blake's daughter?

14:15.354 --> 14:17.948
I grew up with my mom in New York.

14:18.023 --> 14:20.491
I didn't even know who my dad was
until about a year ago.

14:20.559 --> 14:22.925
We talked on the phone for a couple of months.

14:22.995 --> 14:25.589
I never got to meet him in person.

14:25.664 --> 14:28.531
When I heard that Ladyin White
was being moved on the black market...

14:28.601 --> 14:31.001
I came down and got a job with Chandler.

14:31.070 --> 14:33.561
I likeyour heart, Melanie, but, you know,
that painting could be anywhere.

14:33.639 --> 14:35.573
You get caught looking for it, you're dead.

14:35.641 --> 14:39.634
I gotta prove that Chandler's involved.
His security's good.

14:39.712 --> 14:42.510
I thought that I would get him
with that key logger thing.

14:42.581 --> 14:44.742
But I need more access to his files.

14:44.817 --> 14:49.982
Melanie, I'm supposed to check the security
footage from the service entrance tomorrow.

14:50.055 --> 14:52.148
The same oneyou used.

14:52.224 --> 14:54.624
You told him? Look, ifhe sees me--

14:54.693 --> 14:57.685
I'll make sure he doesn't,
provided your story checks out.

14:59.231 --> 15:01.461
My story?

15:01.533 --> 15:04.331
Uh, don't worry about it.
We'll check into it.

15:04.403 --> 15:06.102
?? [Men Singing In Spanish ]

15:06.102 --> 15:07.467
?? [Men Singing In Spanish ]

15:18.414 --> 15:23.113
Yo, Mike. Mikey.
Looks like Melanie was telling the truth.

15:23.185 --> 15:26.211
Had to pull a few favors,
but I was able to get my hands on that.

15:26.288 --> 15:28.688
[Michael]
An apartment lease from 1985.

15:28.757 --> 15:31.248
Yep.
[ Chuckles ]

15:31.327 --> 15:35.320
Check that out.J.D. Blake's signature
right next to Melanie's mom's.

15:35.397 --> 15:38.332
Little loft in Soho.
The math adds up, Mike.

15:38.400 --> 15:40.334
- She's his daughter.
- All right.

15:40.402 --> 15:42.666
Give her a call, tell her I'll help her out.

15:42.738 --> 15:46.572
But tell Melanie she has to stop spying.
I'll handle it.

15:46.642 --> 15:49.008
[Michael Narrating]
To make a magnetpowerful enough...

15:49.078 --> 15:52.377
to wipe a security camera tape
you need a strong powersupply.

15:52.448 --> 15:55.315
A wall outlet will do nicely
ifthere's one available.

15:55.384 --> 16:00.083
But ifyou need something more portable,
a car battery. works in a pinch.

16:00.156 --> 16:03.648
Ofcourse, you have to be careful
to use a heavy-gauge wire...

16:03.726 --> 16:07.628
ifyou don 't want a fiery. explosion
that covers you in battery. acid.

16:07.696 --> 16:10.688
But do it right,
andyou've got a magnet powerful enough...

16:10.766 --> 16:13.894
to wipe any magnetic media
you can manage to get close to.

16:13.969 --> 16:15.630
Mr. Chandler said you were com i ng by.

16:15.704 --> 16:17.365
- You had a break-in?
- Something like that.

16:17.439 --> 16:20.408
We keep all the footage
backed up on the hard drive there.

16:20.476 --> 16:22.444
Should go back about six months.

16:22.511 --> 16:25.912
Ifyou can lay offjust the last few weeks
to DVD, I can go through 'em.

16:25.981 --> 16:29.849
Sure. Or I can do V.H.S.,
not that anybody has those anymore.

16:35.758 --> 16:38.352
It's, uh, not coming up.

16:38.427 --> 16:40.418
What? What's wrong? How doyou mean?

16:40.496 --> 16:43.294
[Tapping Keyboard]

16:43.365 --> 16:46.596
It's not possible.
The drives-- they're wiped.

16:46.669 --> 16:48.933
The footage-- It's all gone.

16:49.004 --> 16:51.472
I better tell Chandler about this right now.

16:51.540 --> 16:54.566
You got a serious problem,
much more serious thanyou led me to believe.

16:54.643 --> 16:57.111
- Now, I need to know--
-J ust slow down.J ust--

16:57.179 --> 17:00.706
You're saying the footage was erased.
I mean, could it be a screw-up on the machine?

17:00.783 --> 17:02.808
I know what it looks like
when a machine screws up...

17:02.885 --> 17:05.547
and I know what it looks like when someone
is erasing theirtracks.

17:05.621 --> 17:07.646
I mean, how could anyone possibly do that?

17:07.723 --> 17:09.588
A crooked security guard, a hacker.

17:09.657 --> 17:11.421
Hell, for all I know...

17:11.492 --> 17:14.290
it could've been some guy
walking in with a-- an electromagnet.

17:14.363 --> 17:16.797
The point is, he's a professional.

17:16.865 --> 17:18.799
You're the security expert.
What do I do about it?

17:18.867 --> 17:21.300
I gotta start with your computers.
I gotta go through everything.

17:21.369 --> 17:24.737
- I gotta see ifyour systems have been breached.
- Oh, yeah.

17:24.807 --> 17:27.275
My computer files?
No, no, no. That's private information.

17:27.343 --> 17:30.642
Do you want me to find this guy
with one hand tied behind my back?

17:30.713 --> 17:34.171
I mean, areyou hoping he walks through
that door, stands in front ofyou and says...

17:34.250 --> 17:36.980
"Hi. I'm your spy"?
[ Chuckling ]

17:37.052 --> 17:40.078
Call me when you're serious.

17:40.155 --> 17:42.180
[Michael Narrating]
Whenyou're playing the role ofspyhunter...

17:42.258 --> 17:44.385
and the personyou're hunting isyourself...

17:44.460 --> 17:47.486
the trail ofevidence
can lead anywhere you say it does.

17:47.563 --> 17:49.554
Wait!

17:51.267 --> 17:54.430
You real ly think access to the computers
will help you find him?

17:54.503 --> 17:56.937
And no one can create more fear...

17:57.006 --> 17:59.497
more paranoia than the spy-hunter.

17:59.575 --> 18:01.440
I hope so.
But I'm gonna be honest with you.

18:01.510 --> 18:03.444
When you're dealing with someone this good...

18:03.512 --> 18:05.707
it could get a lot worse before it gets better.

18:09.585 --> 18:13.351
So I gave Chandler's encrypted files
a deep tissue massage.

18:13.422 --> 18:15.947
- We got his whole life here.
- Anything about the Ladyin White?

18:16.025 --> 18:17.754
Ifhe has it, he hasn't moved ityet...

18:17.826 --> 18:20.386
'cause there's no big cash movements
and he hasn't been doing much offshore.

18:20.462 --> 18:23.022
- Well, there's gotta be something, Sam.
- There's something, all right.

18:23.098 --> 18:25.123
The week Melanie's dad died...

18:25.200 --> 18:27.395
Chandler's calendar had a bunch ofblank spots.

18:27.469 --> 18:30.768
So I cross-referenced that with
the phone records, came up with a guy.

18:30.839 --> 18:34.002
Jacob Orr, a so-called security consultant.

18:34.076 --> 18:37.239
- He did a stint for manslaughter.
- Chandler's wet work guy.

18:37.313 --> 18:39.645
- IfI'm a betting man.
- You wanna make a new friend?

18:39.715 --> 18:44.152
- You can take Fi.
- Oh, boy. You sure know how
to sweeten the pot, Mike.

18:44.219 --> 18:48.781
Hey, uh, speaking of Fi,
what was that whole business at the loft?

18:48.857 --> 18:52.315
You know, with the weird energy?

18:52.394 --> 18:56.023
Oh, no, Mike. Tell meyou didn't.

18:56.098 --> 18:58.032
You did, didn'tyou? You did.

18:58.100 --> 19:00.534
What? No. I don't know whatyou're
talking about. What?

19:00.602 --> 19:03.901
How manytimes doyou have to touch
the flame until you figure out that it burns?

19:03.972 --> 19:05.837
You gonna helpwith thejob or not?

19:05.908 --> 19:09.002
Of course. But I object to the fact
thatyou wanted me to workwith her...

19:09.078 --> 19:11.342
without telling me thatyou were doing
a little booty call.

19:11.413 --> 19:13.404
Check.

19:17.586 --> 19:18.187
[ Slurping ]

19:18.187 --> 19:19.245
[ Slurping ]

19:19.321 --> 19:22.290
[Man ]
Oh,yeah. Thankyou very.much.

19:22.358 --> 19:24.417
[ Exhales ]

19:24.493 --> 19:26.427
- That's our boy.
- Mmm.

19:26.495 --> 19:29.293
- Bigger in person.
- Mmm. Recently divorced.

19:29.365 --> 19:31.026
Lives here at the hotel.

19:31.100 --> 19:33.762
He spends a good chunk
ofhis time bouncing in and out of rehab.

19:36.638 --> 19:40.631
[Chuckles ]
Looks like he's readyforanothervisit.

19:40.709 --> 19:43.075
You sure you're up for this?

19:43.145 --> 19:45.375
Planting a bug in a cell phone.

19:45.447 --> 19:47.915
You think I can't get a guy
to go up to his room?

19:47.983 --> 19:50.713
No, I'd sayyou have a gift
for getting men to make bad choices.

19:50.786 --> 19:53.914
- Michael told you.
- He didn't have to.

19:53.989 --> 19:56.787
Well, don't look at me. He started it.

19:56.859 --> 19:59.828
Fi, Mr. Orr is waiting.

20:04.733 --> 20:06.667
- [ Laughing ]
- [Michael Narrating] Fora female operative...

20:06.735 --> 20:09.602
picking a guyup at a bar
is harderthan it might seem.

20:09.671 --> 20:13.198
Most men have a sense
for when a pickup is going too well.

20:13.275 --> 20:15.675
Ifit's too easy, they get suspicious.

20:15.744 --> 20:17.678
Ifit's too hard, they move on.

20:17.746 --> 20:21.910
U h-uh. Are you serious?
My ex was from Marstown.

20:21.984 --> 20:25.078
Your ex? That means you're single now.

20:25.154 --> 20:28.851
[ Chuckling ]
Now, that's a leading question.

20:28.924 --> 20:31.688
- How's about I buyyou another drink?
- Mmm.

20:31.760 --> 20:35.491
- I really shouldn't.
- Oh, you should.

20:35.564 --> 20:38.761
Or, uh, I could makeyou a drink in my room.

20:41.270 --> 20:44.262
[Michael Narrating]
Once an operative has a guyon the hook...

20:44.339 --> 20:48.366
she needs backup to make sure
things don't go too far.

20:50.546 --> 20:54.676
The proper sedative for cocktail hour
ensures an early evening.

20:54.750 --> 20:59.187
Chloral hydrate is a mild but effective choice.

21:04.326 --> 21:06.760
- It'll do the trick...
- After.

21:06.829 --> 21:10.321
but only ifthe target's
interested in drinking it.

21:12.534 --> 21:16.527
Hey, hey. Hey!
What do you thi nk you're doi n'?

21:16.605 --> 21:19.938
Ifhe's not, you have to induce
unconsciousness some other way.

21:20.008 --> 21:21.669
Not with this shirt on.

21:21.743 --> 21:26.680
I wanna see these big muscles. Mmm.

21:28.984 --> 21:31.976
[ Groans ]

21:32.054 --> 21:36.991
- [Thud]
- [DoorHandle Rattling]

21:37.059 --> 21:40.085
- [Banging On Door]
- You got somebody outside?

21:40.162 --> 21:43.859
You settin' me up, bitch?
[ Groans ]

21:55.210 --> 21:56.871
Oh, come on!

22:02.518 --> 22:04.509
What?

22:11.760 --> 22:14.786
- [Knocking]
- Where's Michael?

22:14.863 --> 22:17.058
Make yourself right at home.

22:17.132 --> 22:20.761
- Where is he?
- He's out getting someyogurt.
Why? What's going on?

22:20.836 --> 22:22.770
That security footage
he erased with the magnet...

22:22.838 --> 22:25.306
Chandler paid to have
the drive sent out to be rebuilt.

22:25.374 --> 22:27.433
Okay, relax. That'll take a while.

22:27.509 --> 22:29.875
Reconstructing data stripped off
a hard drive is kind oflike...

22:29.945 --> 22:33.108
putting a shredded document
back together again, only different.

22:33.181 --> 22:36.810
- We're running out oftime, okay?
By the time he's done, I'm dead.
- We're gettin' close, Melanie.

22:36.885 --> 22:39.911
Chandler hired a guy to do his dirtywork.
We put a bug in his phone.

22:39.988 --> 22:41.956
- This is whatwe heard.
- I'm telling you, Chandler.

22:42.024 --> 22:44.720
The bitch attacked me. She had backup.

22:44.793 --> 22:46.761
[Chandler]
It was probablyjust a robbery..

22:46.828 --> 22:49.456
[ Orr]
A two-man team to steal $40? I'm serious!

22:49.531 --> 22:51.465
Ifsomebodyfound out
about the holding company--

22:51.533 --> 22:54.229
[ Chandler] I got all that stuff
locked up in my office.Just relax.

22:54.303 --> 22:56.271
[ Orr ] I 'll relax
when I got my money.

22:56.338 --> 22:58.363
So, sounds like they set up
a holding company...

22:58.440 --> 23:01.068
to deal with the dirty money
once they sell the painting.

23:01.143 --> 23:04.306
So ifwe can link these documents up
connecting the two ofthem...

23:04.379 --> 23:06.347
that's enough to take to the cops.

23:06.415 --> 23:09.578
How are we gonna get them? Chandler, he
doesn't even let the cleaning crew in anymore.

23:09.651 --> 23:12.142
Well, I think it's time
for Chandler's spy to be more aggressive.

23:13.422 --> 23:15.151
I mean Mike, notyou.

23:16.658 --> 23:18.523
[Knocking]

23:18.594 --> 23:21.688
- Miles.
- What the hell did you get me into?

23:21.763 --> 23:26.928
- What areyou talking about? What?
- They broke into my home--

23:27.002 --> 23:29.027
where I sleep, where I live.

23:29.104 --> 23:30.696
What? You sure it wasn't--

23:30.772 --> 23:33.741
No, no. Maybe the lock
on the door broke itself.

23:33.809 --> 23:36.642
Maybe my files threw themselves around!

23:36.712 --> 23:39.875
- Of course I'm sure.
- Was there anything taken?
Did he find anything thatyou--

23:39.948 --> 23:42.178
No. All the files are encrypted.

23:42.250 --> 23:45.617
They--They're kept off-site.
I talked to some people in the neighborhood.

23:45.687 --> 23:48.781
They said they saw a man and a woman.
It was a two-person team.

23:52.461 --> 23:54.827
What? What is it?

23:54.896 --> 23:58.627
A b--A business associate of mine, he was--
he was approached the same way.

23:58.700 --> 24:00.861
- I thought that he was--
- And you didn't tell me?

24:00.936 --> 24:05.669
Maybe I'm not being clear.
I need to know everything that is going on!

24:05.741 --> 24:09.040
Because now, I'm involved.

24:09.111 --> 24:13.878
- Whoever this guy is, he's got resources, training.
- What kind of person could be--

24:13.949 --> 24:17.385
Could be anybody.
Some spy gets blacklisted, goes freelance.

24:17.452 --> 24:20.148
He could be standing right in front ofyou,
and you wouldn't even know it.

24:20.222 --> 24:21.917
Geez.

24:23.325 --> 24:25.259
I need to know what he's after.

24:25.327 --> 24:27.887
Chandler, you have a mistress?
Fudgeyour tax records?

24:27.963 --> 24:30.932
Steal a pack of gum in the sixth grade?
You have to tell me.

24:30.999 --> 24:33.991
It's the onlywayl can protectyou, protect us.

24:35.971 --> 24:39.964
- No, no. There's nothing. I don't have--
- Nothing.

24:41.376 --> 24:45.210
Okay. Uh, I'm gonna need
to upgrade your system.

24:45.280 --> 24:49.307
I'm gonna lock down your office.
I need access to the camera feeds...

24:49.384 --> 24:52.444
the security codes and the alarms.

24:52.521 --> 24:55.217
You're gonna have to trust me. Chandler.

24:55.290 --> 24:59.158
- You with me?
- Yeah.

25:06.368 --> 25:07.960
[Typing]

25:08.036 --> 25:10.027
[Sam ]
Okay, Mikey, the feeds are up.

25:10.105 --> 25:12.801
You sureyou have to go
through the gallery.?

25:12.874 --> 25:15.434
Well, Chandler's checking
the service entrance cameras.

25:15.510 --> 25:17.603
I don't have much ofa choice.

25:17.679 --> 25:20.204
I'm at the west entrance of the gallery.
Tell me when to go.

25:20.282 --> 25:26.152
Okay, you are clear to get
to the first column... now.

25:28.323 --> 25:31.656
Okay, now there's a camera
on the otherside ofthat column...

25:31.727 --> 25:33.661
and it's sweeping
the north end ofthe gallery..

25:33.729 --> 25:36.664
So on my cue,
I want you to go to the left.

25:36.732 --> 25:39.496
Uh, left. Uh, you sure?

25:39.568 --> 25:42.401
Yeah, Mike, who's the guy who's looking
at the camera here? Yeah, I'm sure.

25:42.471 --> 25:46.407
You're fine. Cameras are moving. Moving.

25:46.475 --> 25:49.273
Here we go. Three, two, one--

25:49.344 --> 25:52.836
No, no, no! It's my left. My left.
Your right. Stop. Stop. Sorry..

25:52.914 --> 25:57.408
Okay. Let's try. this again.
I wantyou to go to your left.

25:57.486 --> 26:02.480
Three, two, one, go.

26:02.557 --> 26:04.491
[ Michael Narrating ]
When it comes to security...

26:04.559 --> 26:06.823
the difference between a spy
and a regular thief...

26:06.895 --> 26:09.329
is that a thiefgets to take
what he wants and run.

26:09.397 --> 26:12.423
A spy has to go back
to the scene ofthe crime the next day...

26:12.501 --> 26:14.526
and act like nothing happened.

26:14.603 --> 26:18.164
It makes the approach a little more delicate.

26:18.240 --> 26:20.174
[ Sam ]
How's it going in there, Mike?

26:20.242 --> 26:23.769
Yeah, there's nothi ng here but certificates
of authenticity for paintings and artwork.

26:23.845 --> 26:27.406
It's gotta be here somewhere.

26:27.482 --> 26:31.475
Whenyou're a spy,youspenda lot oftime
looking forpeople's hidingplaces.

26:31.553 --> 26:35.853
It's always good to start bysearching
where your target has the easiest access.

26:35.924 --> 26:38.654
Ofcourse, smart targets...

26:38.727 --> 26:41.992
don't always hide things
where they have the easiest access.

26:42.063 --> 26:45.157
After that, the search
gets a little more subtle.

26:45.233 --> 26:47.326
You look for signs ofmoved furniture...

26:47.402 --> 26:51.031
marks on the carpet, scuffs on the walls.

26:54.543 --> 26:57.171
Anything out ofplace.

27:14.129 --> 27:17.587
I found where he's hidi ng the papers,
but it's an armored file cabinet.

27:17.666 --> 27:20.362
[Sam ] That's no sweat. We'll come back
with a cutting torch and call it a day.

27:20.435 --> 27:23.734
Yeah, a torch would burn the documents.
I need something more specialized...

27:23.805 --> 27:26.706
Iike a diamond-tip drill bit
with a cooling system.

27:26.775 --> 27:29.744
[ Chortles ]
That sounds like a doozy, Mike.

27:29.811 --> 27:32.473
Look, I can make some calls,
but it's gonna take a couple days.

27:32.547 --> 27:34.777
Let's get on it.

27:34.850 --> 27:39.253
Melanie, we're making progress. We should
have everything we need in a couple of days.

27:39.321 --> 27:41.949
- You just need to sit tight.
- Sit tight?

27:42.023 --> 27:43.615
Chandler is acting weird.

27:43.692 --> 27:45.626
He's walking around the office...

27:45.694 --> 27:48.026
staring at all the employees,
checking people's desks.

27:48.096 --> 27:50.326
That means he's getting paranoid.
That's good.

27:50.398 --> 27:54.129
- The worse it gets,
the more he turns to Michael for help.
- What ifhe knows?

27:54.202 --> 27:57.365
There's no wayhe rebuilt the securityfootage
from those hard drivesyet.

27:57.439 --> 27:59.907
No, the most important thing
is foryou to just act completely normal.

27:59.975 --> 28:02.967
- Pretend that nothing's going on.
- I'll try.

28:03.044 --> 28:06.036
I gotta run.
It's nice meeting you, Fiona.

28:06.114 --> 28:08.105
You too.

28:10.185 --> 28:14.554
You know, pretending nothing's going on
is easier for some people than others.

28:16.191 --> 28:19.854
- [ Cell Phone Rings ]
- [ Beeps ]

28:19.928 --> 28:22.488
- What have you got, Seymour?
- I'llshowyou what I got.

28:22.564 --> 28:25.124
Tell Fiona to fire up the Saab, dude.
We're gonna need room for three.

28:27.736 --> 28:31.103
Your bomber is holed up
in that little cottage right there.

28:31.172 --> 28:35.438
His girlfriendrun overthis morning
fora little, uh...

28:35.510 --> 28:37.501
together time.

28:47.756 --> 28:49.690
[Fiona ]
Boobytrap on the door.

28:49.758 --> 28:52.420
I guess he's not expecting any more visitors.

28:52.494 --> 28:54.359
That's no problem.

28:54.429 --> 28:56.920
I got the shotguns and those
breaching rounds I brought.

28:56.998 --> 28:59.193
They'l I cut through that wall
like it's cardboard.

28:59.267 --> 29:02.361
[Michael] That would make a little
bigger bang than we want.

29:02.437 --> 29:06.373
The door isn't the only thing
rigged to blow. Look.

29:06.441 --> 29:11.538
I'm gonna do some scouting,
figure out a better route for an approach.

29:11.613 --> 29:13.205
Fi.
[ Mouths Words ]

29:17.118 --> 29:20.747
Man. That guy.

29:20.822 --> 29:23.552
I mean, it's like he sees
around corners, you know?

29:23.625 --> 29:25.820
[ Chuckles ]

29:25.894 --> 29:29.057
So what's up with you two?
You're not together anymore?

29:33.168 --> 29:36.899
We're in, uh, different spaces, Seymour.

29:36.972 --> 29:39.964
Different spaces? Give me a break.

29:40.041 --> 29:44.137
As a practitioner oftai chi,
let me tell you something, missy.

29:44.212 --> 29:47.147
Go with the flow ofthe universe.

29:47.215 --> 29:49.843
All right? It's destiny, you two.

29:49.918 --> 29:51.852
Forces biggerthan us.

29:51.920 --> 29:56.721
Don't argue with destiny.
It will kickyour ass.

29:56.791 --> 29:59.851
[ Sighs ]
Believe me.

30:03.098 --> 30:05.464
I'll keep that in mind, Seymour.

30:12.838 --> 30:16.069
I can drink this outside
ifyou two need some alone time.

30:17.742 --> 30:20.006
Drink it here, Sam.

30:20.078 --> 30:23.013
- So, Seymour find your bomber?
- Yeah.

30:23.081 --> 30:26.881
The place he's staying at is wired to blow
ifwe so much as knock on the window.

30:26.952 --> 30:30.319
Yikes. Well, in other news,
I got a lead on a precision drill...

30:30.388 --> 30:32.515
we can use on Chandler's file cabinet.

30:32.591 --> 30:36.425
- Buddy's gonna give us a break.
- [ Cell Phone Rings ]

30:36.494 --> 30:38.985
- Yeah, Melanie, what's going on?
- I'm at the office.

30:39.064 --> 30:41.965
- I found something.
- You're at the office? You're not supposed to--

30:42.033 --> 30:43.967
I was talking to a girlfriend from work.

30:44.035 --> 30:46.663
She told me that Chandler's secretary
was shredding, like, a ton of paperwork.

30:46.738 --> 30:49.036
But get this. Secretary didn't finish.

30:49.107 --> 30:51.041
She left a ton of paperwork for Monday.

30:51.109 --> 30:53.043
So, I've been going through the files until--

30:53.111 --> 30:55.045
You're at the office on a weekend?

30:55.113 --> 30:57.946
Ifyou used your employee security code,
Chandlerwill knowyou're there.

30:58.016 --> 31:01.577
What else was I supposed to do? This stuff
could be gone, and then we'll never know.

31:01.653 --> 31:05.612
Melanie, he's not gonna just leave
documents lying around for someone to find.

31:05.690 --> 31:07.885
- What doyou mean?
- It's a trap.

31:07.959 --> 31:10.621
He knowsyou're there.
You need to get out right now.

31:10.695 --> 31:12.959
[ Vehicle Approaches ]

31:14.366 --> 31:16.834
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

31:16.902 --> 31:18.893
He's here.

31:22.307 --> 31:24.935
Melanie, listen to me very carefully.
Are you in the copy room?

31:25.010 --> 31:26.602
Yeah, I am.

31:26.678 --> 31:29.647
Get a box of paper, some duct tape
and an extension cord.

31:29.714 --> 31:32.012
Some duct tape and an extension cord?

31:32.083 --> 31:34.278
Tape the cell phone to the top ofthe box...

31:34.352 --> 31:37.014
and run a wire behind it
and put it in the gallery entrance.

31:37.088 --> 31:38.749
Do it now. I'm on myway.

31:38.823 --> 31:41.018
- Fi, you got explosives?
- I'll pretend you didn't ask that.

31:41.092 --> 31:44.118
- I have to take a more direct
approach with Chandler.
- I like the sound ofthat.

31:44.195 --> 31:46.163
- Mike, you want me to come with you?
- Uh, no.

31:46.231 --> 31:48.961
- I wantyou to get in touch
with Chandler's hit man.
- [DoorAlarm Chiming]

31:54.940 --> 31:58.000
[ Cell Phone Rings ]

31:58.076 --> 32:00.340
